Step after setting up mainnetfork Example
                                   3             5
                     1 2           4             6                            
         ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ + ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ + ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ + ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ─ ▶ Time (DAY)
                     W1            W2            W3
Move blocktimestamp to W1 (Assuming W1 is next week) and Deployer call checkpointToken to move lastTokenTimestamp to W1. command to move to start week and deployer call checkpoint
$ yarn task:set-timestamp-startweek
$ yarn task:checkpoint --grasshouseaddress <addressOfGrassHoue>
Someone lock ALPACA at [W1 + 1 day] command to advance 1 day
$ yarn task:advancetime --days 1
Move timestamp to W2 command to move to week 2
$ yarn task:set-timestamp-startweek
Deployer call checkpoint to move lastTokenTimestamp to W2 to allocate rewards to W2 only. Deployer call feed() to feed token to GrassHouse. Enable canCheckpointToken. command to checkpoint, feed token to grasshouse, enable canCheckpointToken
$ yarn task:checkpoint --grasshouseaddress <addressOfGrassHouse>
$ yarn task:feed-grasshouse --grasshouseaddress <addressOfGrassHose> --grasshousetokenaddress <addressOfToken> --amount <amountToBeFeedGrassHouse>
$ yarn task:enable-checkpoint --grasshouseaddress <addressOfGrassHouse>
Move timestamp to W3 command to move to week 3
$ yarn task:set-timestamp-startweek
Call checkpointTotalSupply to allocate reward command to call checkpointTokenSupply
$ yarn task:checkpoint-total-supply --grasshouseaddress <addressOfGrassHouse>
